-- Hollande’s Approval Rating Rises More Than Sarkozy’s, Poll Shows
-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s
-- 2012-04-09T15:34:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/hollande-s-approval-rating-rises-more-than-sarkozy-s-poll-shows.html
Socialist challenger  Francois Hollande ’s approval rating rose more than President Nicolas Sarkozy’s did in April before the French presidential election,
according to a poll by Ipsos for Le Point magazine.  Hollande’s rating this month gained four points to 57
percent while Sarkozy’s climbed two points to 40 percent, the
pollster said today in a statement. The president’s disapproval
rating fell 1 point to 58 percent in the period, according to
the poll. Hollande’s disapproval rating in April was 40 percent.  Ipsos questioned 955 people on April 6-7. No margin of
error was given.  France  holds two rounds of voting on April 22
and May 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
